Camera, Lights, Pose, Selfie time! We all love a good selfie, at least most of us do and rightfully so considering it was named the international Word of the Year 2013 by Oxford Dictionaries in both the UK and US. Selfie as it known is “a photograph that one has taken of oneself, typically one taken with a smartphone or webcam and uploaded to a social media website,” There is so much buzz surrounding selfies that Time Magazine in 2012 included it in its top 10 buzzwords for that year and its use has skyrocketed As selfies continue to remain relevant till present day 2019, here are some interesting facts you should know about 2013’s word of the year. Now that you know some facts about selfies, maybe when next you want to take you’re a selfie, you can pose with more knowledge. Have a selfie swell time!